    • HIGH_NUMBER_OF_OBSERVED_PREDICTED_PATHOGENIC_VARIANTS

      public static final GenotypeLrMatchType HIGH_NUMBER_OF_OBSERVED_PREDICTED_PATHOGENIC_VARIANTS
      Heuristic for the case where we have more called pathogenic variants than we should have in a gene without a high background count -- we will model this as technical error and will take the observed path weighted count to not be more than λdisease. this will have the effect of not down-weighting these genes the user will have to judge whether one of the variants is truly pathogenic.

    • LIRICAL_GT_MODEL

      public static final GenotypeLrMatchType LIRICAL_GT_MODEL
      Gene scored using LIRICAL genotype LR model.

      For more details, consult the Material and Methods | Likelihood Ratio for Genotypes section of the LIRICAL manuscript.
